### Version Control
* Use a tool to track every version of every file
* Automatically track pending changes being made
* Allows multiple people to share code
* Accounts for 25-30% of your productivity


### Version Control - Getting Started 
* Sign up at Github
* Create a repository
* Use Github Desktop to get code on your local computer
* Commit your code changes as you work


### Version Control - Github
* Web service that tracks your code
* Holds your code repositories
* Connects your local code with the master copy of your code
* Lets your share code with others


### Version Control - Create a repository
* Stores all versions of all files
* Lets you review changes and roll back when needed
* Repositories are cloned onto multiple computers
* All computers have all of the code


### Version Control - Github Desktop
* Use Github Desktop to get code on your local computer
* Install on each computer you use
* Clone your repository onto your computer
* Sync the code with Pull and Push


### Version Control - Commit Changes
* Modify files
* Commit changes 
* Sync the code with Pull and Push
* View history of changes



