## BUILD

![](img/Bear_Logo.png)

---

### Steps setup Version Control
* Register for Github account
* Create a Github repository
* Setup Github Desktop
* Clone Your Repo 
* Commit changes
    

### Register for Github account
* Visit [Github.com](https://github.com) and sign up for a free account
* You must pay if you want Private repositories 


### Create a Github repository
* Create a repo

[New Repo screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs200/git-new-repo.png)

* Setup the settings you want

[Repo Settings screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs200/git-repo-settings.png)


### Setup Github Desktop
* Example of Github Desktop

[Github Desktop screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs200/GithubDesktop.png)


### Clone Your Repo 
* Clone Your repository onto your computer
* Setup Windows file location - Recommend "Documents/UNC_BACS_200"
* Change your Filezilla setting for local directory to match


### Commit changes
* From Start Menu launch Github Desktop
* Pin to taskbar
* View the changes to your files
* Capture a screen shot of your pending changes
* Commit the changes with a commit message
* Push the code back to the Github server

Example of pending changes

[Clone Repo screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs200/git-changes.png)


### View Change History
* Changes to be committed

[Commit History screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs200/git-history.png)

* Change History

[Commit Changes screenshot](/static/images/unc/bacs200/git-view-commits.png)

    
